But I’m not going back yet.

496
00:41:58,656 --> 00:42:03,456
Right now, our company is working on a big project that requires a co-investment with a maker in Japan.

497
00:42:04,776 --> 00:42:06,496
Do you want to try working there?

498
00:42:07,136 --> 00:42:10,376
Hmm, sounds interesting.

499
00:42:10,576 --> 00:42:12,376
What do I have to do?

500
00:42:12,536 --> 00:42:15,736
Poj: You only have to monitor the manufacturing process there for about 3 months.

501
00:42:16,456 --> 00:42:18,416
But if you can get it done earlier than scheduled,

502
00:42:18,656 --> 00:42:21,496
I’ll let you manage our branch in Japan too.

503
00:42:22,056 --> 00:42:26,056
So that you won’t have to come back to Thailand yet. Is that good?

504
00:42:29,176 --> 00:42:29,976
Okay.

505
00:42:30,696 --> 00:42:33,256
Poj: All right then. We’ll talk more about this later.

506
00:42:34,136 --> 00:42:34,936
Yes.

507
00:43:29,736 --> 00:43:32,336
[Fukuoka Airport International Terminal] / [Taxi]

508
00:43:32,576 --> 00:43:37,336
Yatsu-san: Pheem! Over here, please. Hello, good afternoon.

509
00:43:42,496 --> 00:43:44,416
The car park is that way.

510
00:43:44,936 --> 00:43:48,256
Wow, I can’t believe it. You can speak Thai?

511
00:43:48,256 --> 00:43:52,416
Oh, I’m fluent in Thai...with moderate English, and a bit Japanese.

512
00:43:52,416 --> 00:43:54,376
Toyota, Honda, Semagute.

513
00:43:55,616 --> 00:43:59,856
Where’s Olan, the manufacturing MD my dad has told him to pick me up?

514
00:43:59,856 --> 00:44:03,736
Oh, Mr. Olan is in a big meeting about the project that Miss…

515
00:44:04,096 --> 00:44:07,096
I’m sorry, I mean the VP has to take care of.

516
00:44:07,096 --> 00:44:09,616
That’s why he sent me to pick you up instead.

517
00:44:09,696 --> 00:44:10,456
Yes.

518
00:44:10,456 --> 00:44:12,536
What’s our plan for today?

519
00:44:12,776 --> 00:44:17,816
The VP is scheduled to monitor work at the company for 2 days.

520
00:44:18,416 --> 00:44:23,616
After that, we’ll move to another city next week and stay there for 3 months.

521
00:44:23,856 --> 00:44:25,336
That’s where our factory is.

522
00:44:25,376 --> 00:44:28,496
Will you also be there during the entire 3 months, Yatsu-san?

523
00:44:28,496 --> 00:44:30,736
Oh, I’m afraid no.

524
00:44:30,736 --> 00:44:34,096
But the VP has to…

525
00:44:34,096 --> 00:44:37,056
work with our production engineering manager there.

526
00:44:37,336 --> 00:44:41,416
Mr. Poj has assigned her to work with you.

527
00:44:41,936 --> 00:44:45,496
So, I have to learn my job from an engineer?

528
00:44:45,576 --> 00:44:48,016
Yes, but this one is really talented.

529
00:44:48,296 --> 00:44:51,136
Yatsu-san: She’s in charge for this project.

530
00:44:51,576 --> 00:44:55,336
You’ll definitely learn a lot of things from her.

531
00:44:55,616 --> 00:44:59,416
Wow, she must be someone my dad really trusts.

532
00:44:59,416 --> 00:45:00,976
Yes, she’s like his shogun.

533
00:45:04,016 --> 00:45:04,896
Okay.

534
00:45:04,896 --> 00:45:07,256
You’ll see her when we go to the office.

535
00:45:07,256 --> 00:45:10,976
I’ll drop you off at the hotel first.

536
00:45:11,496 --> 00:45:13,296
Then we can go to the office later on.

537
00:45:13,296 --> 00:45:15,816
We can go straight to the office. I’m not tired.

538
00:45:15,816 --> 00:45:20,376
But please stop by at the drug store for me, I just need to buy eye drops and some personal stuff first.

539
00:45:20,456 --> 00:45:22,656
The drug store is close to the office.

540
00:45:22,856 --> 00:45:25,056
So is your hotel.

541
00:45:25,376 --> 00:45:27,336
They are in a walking distance.

542
00:45:27,856 --> 00:45:29,096
Let’s go then, shall we?

543
00:45:29,256 --> 00:45:29,616
Yes.

544
00:45:29,616 --> 00:45:30,856
Come.

545
00:45:56,336 --> 00:45:57,736
Please take your time.

546
00:45:58,136 --> 00:46:03,616
I’ll check you in and put your luggage at the hotel for you.

547
00:46:04,176 --> 00:46:05,856
I’ll wait for you in the car.

548
00:46:05,856 --> 00:46:07,936
Yes, thank you, Yatsu-san.

549
00:46:07,936 --> 00:46:08,176
You’re welcome.

550
00:46:08,176 --> 00:46:09,296
Arigato gazaimasu (Thank you).

551
00:46:09,296 --> 00:46:11,376
Yes, arigato gazaimasu.

552
00:47:15,176 --> 00:47:17,696
I’m sorry, I’m so busy these days I can’t pick you up myself.

553
00:47:18,256 --> 00:47:20,096
Does Yatsu-san take good care of you?

554
00:47:20,536 --> 00:47:21,336
Yes.

555
00:47:22,376 --> 00:47:26,256
This branch is where we use for trading products from Japan to Thailand.

556
00:47:26,576 --> 00:47:29,336
Our company has one particular product which is a bestseller here.

557
00:47:29,896 --> 00:47:32,896
That’s why we decided to take over the manufacturing factory in Japan…

558
00:47:33,456 --> 00:47:36,416
five years ago in order to reduce the cost of importing products.

559
00:47:36,696 --> 00:47:39,056
This product is still a bestseller right now.

560
00:47:39,256 --> 00:47:42,376
So, we are planning to manufacture a similar product line in Thailand.

561
00:47:42,376 --> 00:47:44,016
This would help reduce the shipping cost too.

562
00:47:44,536 --> 00:47:47,056
Wow, sounds very interesting indeed.

563
00:47:47,256 --> 00:47:50,896
So, the most important role goes to the production engineering team.

564
00:47:51,216 --> 00:47:52,616
Actually, they’ve already started meeting since yesterday.

565
00:47:52,736 --> 00:47:53,696
Let’s go inside.

566
00:47:53,696 --> 00:47:54,656
Okay.

567
00:47:55,016 --> 00:47:56,936
Hello.

568
00:48:03,256 --> 00:48:06,216
This is our engineering manager.

569
00:48:21,096 --> 00:48:21,896
Kie!

570
00:48:22,336 --> 00:48:24,976
By the way, I forgot to tell you…

571
00:48:25,096 --> 00:48:28,096
that Kiran will be your mentor during these 3 months.

572
00:48:30,656 --> 00:48:32,976
Welcome, Pheem.

573
00:48:50,576 --> 00:48:52,216
Next, please.

574
00:49:05,896 --> 00:49:08,496
[Kiran Pipittayaphongsa]

575
00:49:11,016 --> 00:49:13,296
Excuse me, everyone.

576
00:49:13,296 --> 00:49:16,336
Can I please interview this candidate alone?

577
00:49:18,696 --> 00:49:19,696
Thank you.

578
00:49:38,936 --> 00:49:45,176
Honestly, I never expected you’d dare to apply for a job here, Kiran.

579
00:49:45,736 --> 00:49:51,816
Being able to work here is one of my first priorities in life.

580
00:49:52,136 --> 00:49:55,256
You’re still very determined and as blunt as usual.

581
00:49:55,976 --> 00:49:57,616
It’s been 3 years now.

582
00:49:57,856 --> 00:50:01,616
I thought you might have changed your mind about a lot of things.

583
00:50:02,456 --> 00:50:05,696
Time can never change my thoughts and feelings.

584
00:50:07,856 --> 00:50:09,496
Let’s start our interview then.

585
00:50:10,336 --> 00:50:10,856
Yes.

586
00:50:11,376 --> 00:50:14,976
You have the highest score in a written exam.

587
00:50:15,696 --> 00:50:17,296
Everything is qualified.

588
00:50:19,696 --> 00:50:21,456
You also scored well during the first interview.

589
00:50:22,336 --> 00:50:23,976
I only have one question for you.

590
00:50:25,856 --> 00:50:28,736
Why do you want to work for our company?

591
00:50:29,336 --> 00:50:33,576
Because working here is the only chance…

592
00:50:35,016 --> 00:50:38,856
to see Pheem when she comes back.

593
00:50:40,376 --> 00:50:44,456
That’s not exactly an answer I’d want to hear to accept your application.

594
00:50:45,736 --> 00:50:48,496
But since you’re Miss Kimheng’s granddaughter,

595
00:50:49,976 --> 00:50:52,096
I’ll give you another chance.

596
00:50:52,816 --> 00:50:54,936
I insist on the same answer.

597
00:50:54,976 --> 00:50:58,896
At least, I want to help Pheem to do her best at work.

598
00:51:00,216 --> 00:51:01,016
Okay.

599
00:51:02,016 --> 00:51:06,696
I agree to hire you as a production engineer.

600
00:51:08,296 --> 00:51:09,256
Thank you.

601
00:51:09,816 --> 00:51:14,256
Good. Now, let’s see when Pheem gets to see you again,

602
00:51:15,136 --> 00:51:19,016
what will she do to the person who used to hurt her so badly?

603
00:51:19,896 --> 00:51:24,976
I hope you’ll let her decide about that on her own.

604
00:51:25,976 --> 00:51:30,856
I also hope you won’t forget the promise you gave me.

605
00:51:32,656 --> 00:51:36,056
Okay. You can start next week.

606
00:51:36,056 --> 00:51:38,416
[HANIKAMU COMPANY]

607
00:51:52,816 --> 00:51:54,936
I get to work at Pheem’s dad’s company now.

608
00:51:57,496 --> 00:52:02,136
I’ll be looking forward to the day we meet again.

609
00:52:03,776 --> 00:52:08,616
I hope your feelings for me are still the same.

